h3. Summary
Pipelines endpoint in API 2 is case sensitive

h3. Steps to Reproduce
For a repository, &#x27;myrepo&#x27;, that belongs to a team with the username &#x27;myTeam&#x27;, run the following:

{code}
#!python

curl --request GET --user username:password https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/myteam/myrepo/pipelines
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The query returns the pipelines for this repo.

h3. Actual Results
The response is:

{code}
#!python

{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "Resource not found", "detail": "There is no API hosted at this URL.\n\nFor information about our API&#x27;s, please refer to the documentation at: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/"}}
{code}

We have next bitbucket-pipelines configuration:

{code}
#!yaml

image:
  name: maven:latest

pipelines:
  tags:
    prod-*:
      - step:
          script:
            - mvn clean install
{code}

If we create tag (&#x27;prod-v0.0.1&#x27;) for some commit in Bitbucket web interface, that pipeline task does not start, in the same time when we create tag on local copy and manually push it to remote, like this:

{code}
#!bash

git tag prod-v0.0.2
git push origin prod-v0.0.2

{code}

that starts and works well. So it looks like web interface does not send push while tag creation.

If you create a pull request and tick the "close branch" feature and then merge the branch. The resulting pipeline build will fail while attempting to clone the repo.

This is because the clone command explictly mentions the now deleted branch: {{git clone --branch="feature/branch" ...}}

I can understand why it&#x27;s being done... but it might be better to try and do the shallow clone of the branch, or if that fails do a full clone and checkout of the correct commit.

Hello.

When I try to run this query:

{code}
"/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<PROJECT>/refs/branches?q=type%3D%22branch%22+and++name%3D%22branch1%22++OR++name%3D%22branch2%22+&format=json"
{code}

I am getting this:

{code}
string(146) "{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "unsupported operand type(s) for |: &#x27;function&#x27; and &#x27;Condition&#x27;", "id": "ac110aa5597940ee89b1030cda770a82"}}"
{code}

It works fine for one branch:

{code}
/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<PROJECT>/refs/branches?q=type%3D%22branch%22+and++name%3D%22branch1%22+&format=json
{code}

According to documentation I should be able to do it:\\
https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/meta/filtering#query-ref

Thank you and have a nice day.
